channel.title: I-Dosing works? (gates of Hades and Hand of God)
channel.description:
I've heard today from soem friends that they saw something on youtube abouth some kind of music that makes you high and halucast stuff (and getting scared and that shit.)
I went on youtube to see it and they actualy act strange after it stops but the commenst are then: FAKE!
I found the sound then on youtube and listned to it bud i only got headaches and my head was bouncing like hell. After that i searched on google abouth it and i found out that you need to buy it for 199$ -The music is 30 mins long and on youtube 10 mins- (i think ppl already can get it free from torrent shit) and you need there free program (they say that with the program, you get more stuff to hear from the sound and you halucast more and more.)
Could this all be real or is this just a huge wast of money?
Some links:
The sound on youtube: [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fuRRkiaw338&feature=related]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fuRRkiaw338&feature=related[/url] The store thingy: [url=http://i-doser.com/storev3/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=277]http://i-doser.com/storev3/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=277[/url] Other I-Doser thingy: [url=http://i-doser.com/storev3/index.php?main_page=product_info&cPath=83&products_id=261]http://i-doser.com/storev3/index.php?main_page=product_info&cPath=83&products_id=261[/url] Some story: [url=http://hellhive.blogspot.com/2009/04/gate-of-hades-experience.html]http://hellhive.blogspot.com/2009/04/gate-of-hades-experience.html[/url]

item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

It’s just a scam using drugs for a marketing tool. The binaural beats may aid in relaxing or stimulating you, but you won’t experience anything close to a high from real drugs. You can’t just listen to it on youtube. And chances are that your earphones don’t play the right frequencies anyways.
